  "summary": "Concrete CMS is Vulnerable to Reflected XSS in Legacy Pagination",
  "details": "Concrete CMS 9.5.0 and below is vulnerable to Reflected XSS in Legacy Pagination via HTML attribute injection. Concrete\\Core\\Legacy\\Pagination builds pagination links by raw-interpolating its $URL field into href=\"\" (<a href=\"{$linkURL}\" …>). Any authenticated admin or report viewer with access to `/dashboard/reports/forms/legacy` who clicks the crafted URL fires the payload in their session.",
